## Browser-as-sandbox: existing security model, repurposed for agents
direction: down

intro: {
  shape: text
  label: "Browser security has 25+ years of\nbattle-tested isolation: same-origin policy,\nCORS, sandboxed iframes, OS process sandbox,\ncross-site cookie isolation, etc."
  style.italic: true
  style.font-color: "#7c3aed"
}

setups: {
  direction: right
  agent_local: {
    label: "❌ Local-machine agent\n(traditional model)"
    shape: rectangle
    style.fill: "#fecaca"
    style.stroke: "#dc2626"
    body: {label: "Agent has access to:\n• Your OS shell\n• Your file system\n• Your installed credentials\n• All your apps\n\nBlast radius:\n= your whole computer"; shape: text}
  }
  agent_browser: {
    label: "✅ Browser-sandboxed agent\n(Operator, browser-use-style)"
    shape: rectangle
    style.fill: "#bbf7d0"
    style.stroke: "#16a34a"
    body: {label: "Agent runs in a browser tab\n(usually remote / cloud).\n\nIt can ONLY do what a browser\ntab can do: navigate URLs, click,\ntype, see DOM.\n\nBlast radius:\n= what that tab's logged-in\n  sessions can do"; shape: text}
  }
}

benefits: {
  label: "Benefits of browser-as-sandbox"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#dbeafe"
  style.stroke: "#2563eb"
  body: {label: "• Cross-site isolation is FREE (browser built-in)\n• No access to your local filesystem\n• No access to your local credentials/keys\n• Easy to revoke (close tab, end session)\n• Compatible with existing 2FA / OAuth\n• User can WATCH the agent work"; shape: text}
}

risks: {
  label: "Remaining risks"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fef3c7"
  style.stroke: "#d97706"
  body: {label: "• Agent reads untrusted web pages\n  (Leg 2 of lethal trifecta still present)\n• If logged into apps, Leg 1 still present\n• Agent can take actions in those apps\n  (so Leg 3 effectively present too)\n→ still need per-action permission gating"; shape: text}
}

intro -> setups
setups -> benefits
benefits -> risks
